# plugin-quality-gates

This plugin ships **two distinct manifests**. Keep both consistent and aligned with their respective schemas.

## 1. `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json` — Cursor plugin manifest

This is what Cursor reads when a user runs `/add-plugin https://github.com/huyhieu2k5/mautoma-agent`.

Rules:

- File MUST live at exactly `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json` (no other path).
- Required: `name` (lowercase kebab-case, regex `^[a-z0-9]([a-z0-9.-]*[a-z0-9])?$`).
- Recommended: `displayName`, `description`, `version`, `author.name`, `license`, `keywords`.
- `author` MUST be an object `{ name, email? }`, NOT a string.
- Path fields (`rules`, `skills`, `agents`, `commands`, `hooks`, `mcpServers`) must be string-or-array-of-strings (paths/globs), NEVER bare names.
- `hooks` is either a string (path to hooks.json) or an inline object — not an array of names.
- Cursor schema is **strict (`additionalProperties: false`)**. Do NOT add custom top-level fields such as `capabilities`, `capabilityDescriptions`, `mandatorySecurity`, `runtime`, `distribution`, `installCommand`, `scripts`, `security`, or `dependencies` to the Cursor manifest. Move those (if any) to `app-manifest.json` instead.
- All paths in the manifest must be repo-relative, no `..`, no absolute paths.

## 2. `app-manifest.json` — npm/runtime app manifest

App-level metadata used by the `npm` scripts and the runtime CLI. NOT read by Cursor.

- Lives at `app-manifest.json` (was previously `plugin.json` — renamed in v1.0.1 to avoid Cursor confusion).
- Free-form shape, but `name` must match `package.json`.

## SKILL.md frontmatter

Every `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` MUST have YAML frontmatter:

```yaml
---
name: <kebab-name>            # lowercase letters, numbers, hyphens — MUST match parent folder
description: "<single-line>"  # one-liner telling the agent when to use it
# optional:
disable-model-invocation: true
paths: ["**/*.ts"]            # glob(s) scoping when this skill applies
---
```

Keep `description` on a single line for safe YAML parsing.

## .mdc rules

Cursor auto-loads `.mdc` files from the path declared in `plugin.json.rules`. Plain `.md` files are NOT picked up.

- `rules/<name>.mdc` with frontmatter `description` + `alwaysApply` (and optional `globs`) is the supported form.
- Do NOT reference absolute filesystem paths (e.g. `@c:\Users\...`) inside a rule — those will be broken on every other user's machine. Use repo-relative paths or describe the resource by its manifest entry.

## hooks.json

Cursor reads `.cursor/hooks.json` with **required `version: 1`**. Session-start driver lives at `scripts/session-start-driver.cjs`; reference it as `"command": "node ./scripts/session-start-driver.cjs"` from the hooks file.

The driver MUST resolve the plugin root via `process.cwd()` or `__dirname` (already does), not by hardcoding absolute paths.

## Common mistakes to avoid

- ❌ Hardcoding `c:\Users\...` or `~/my-projects/...` in any rule, hook, or README.
- ❌ Adding custom top-level fields to `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json` — Cursor will reject it.
- ❌ Pointing `skills` / `agents` / `rules` at an array of bare names instead of paths.
- ❌ Putting `plugin.json` at repo root and expecting Cursor to find it (it won't — must be `.cursor-plugin/plugin.json`).
